<div tiddler="LakoffJohnsonOnTruth" modifier="ESpringer" modified="200509192002" created="200509192002" tags="epigraphs excludeLists">!!Because our ''conceptual systems'' grow out of our bodies, meaning is ''grounded in and though our bodies''. Because a vast range of our concepts are [[metaphorical|metaphors]], meaning is ''not entirely literal'' and the classical correspondence theory of truth is false. ... That does not mean that truth is purely subjective... Rather, our [[common embodidiment|social affordances]] allows for common, ''stable truths''.\n!!!!-- Lakoff and Johnson, //Philosophy in the Flesh// 1999</div>